.nh
.TH bls-btrfs-snapshots 1
.SH NAME
bls-btrfs-snapshots \- Write BLS Type #1 entries for btrfs snapshots

.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbls-btrfs-snapshots\fP [\fIglobal options\fP] \fICOMMAND\fP [\fIargs\fP]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Discover btrfs snapshots and emit BLS Type #1 entries under
/loader/entries/, consumed by systemd-boot or BLS-aware GRUB.

.PP
Only ESP-mode snapshots are emitted: systemd-boot cannot traverse btrfs
subvolumes to reach kernels inside a snapshot. Use refind-btrfs-snapshots
for btrfs-mode coverage via rEFInd's btrfs driver.

.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.EX
  -c, --config string      Path to config file (default: /etc/bls-btrfs-snapshots.yaml)
      --log-level string   Log verbosity: trace, debug, info, warn, error
.EE

.SH COMMANDS
.SS bls-btrfs-snapshots generate
Write BLS Type #1 entries for btrfs snapshots

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP \fBbls-btrfs-snapshots generate [flags]\fR

.PP
\fBOptions:\fP

.EX
      --dry-run   Show what would be written without making changes
      --force     Force generation even if booted from a snapshot
  -y, --yes       Automatically approve all changes without prompting
.EE

.SS bls-btrfs-snapshots version
Print version information

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP \fBbls-btrfs-snapshots version\fR

.SH SEE ALSO
refind-btrfs-snapshots(1), kernel-spy(1)
